SIMPLE: hypostasize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypostasize
<hw>Hy*pos"ta*size</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make into
a distinct substance; to conceive or treat as an existing being; to
hypostatize.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pressed Newtonians . . . refused to <qex>hypostasize</qex> the
law of gravitation into an ether.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Hypostatical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hypostatic</ent>⟦br⟧
